<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collected_item_association  
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association">
A <b>Collected_item_association</b> is a mechanism to associate <b>Item_instance objects</b> with a <b>Collection_definition</b>.

A <b>Collected_item_association</b> is a type of <b>Item_definition_instance_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collected_item_association  Attribute: relating_view 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.relating_view"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.relating_view">
The <b>relating_view</b> specifies the <b>Collection_definition</b> that collects the Item_instance objects.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collected_item_association  Attribute: related_view 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.related_view"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.related_view">
The <b>related_view</b> specifies the Item_instance objects that are in the <b>Collection_definition</b> instance.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collection_definition  
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition">
A <b>Collection_definition</b> is the definition of an <b>Item_version</b> that serves as a collector for Item_instance objects that are mounted in the same product but may not be assembled together. 
<example>Handles on the left and right doors, locks and keys of a shelf all from one supplier, wooden panels from the same supplier (to ensure common structure of the wood) are examples for collections.
</example>

A <b>Collection_definition</b> is a type of <b>Design_discipline_item_definition.</b>
</ext_description>
